Very good game. However background progression. Is incredibly slow. 60k 
(60a in game) gold an hour and 1200 stages while playing "actively", while 
only about 1.2k gold and a handful of stages an hour if the game isn't the 
main window, such as when watching YouTube or on Facebook. If you don't 
have an additional device to keep the game in focus 24/7 on I would have 
trouble suggesting this game. The game also consumes battery faster than 
YouTube or pubg mobile so being near a charger is a necessity for sessions 
longer than 3 hours ( at least for my 3200 capacity battery in a Stylo 3). 
The tutorial could use a little bit of work in some aspects, but the 
community is very helpful in the English chat channel so it's a bit of a 
non-issue. And I would be more than willing to give the developer feedback 
and help with the tutorial through the dev feedback button in game. From 
what I hear he is an understanding guy willing to improve his product for 
his playerbase when he has time. If background progress or battery 
consumption issues are dealt with in an impactful way, I would immediately 
change my review to 5 stars. The gameplay is interesting, the art is a 
beautiful retro style, and the community is helpful and present. The issues 
listed are really the only issues with the game, as long as this type of 
game is what you are looking for.

Overall a great game. Currency is balanced and premium currency isn't 
terribly hard to obtain so progress is achievable without paying. Kind of 
confusing when you start, but you get the game after a while. Graphics are 
great and the pixel are is top notch. Gameplay is fun, but for some people 
it might seem a bit repetitive. The fastest way to actually progress is to 
leave your device on running the game while upgrading stuff from time to 
time. (Though I hesitate to do this because it probably isn't that good for 
your device.) (Review ends here. After this is suggestions to the 
developers.) Some features I would like to see added are extra buttons 
(like a reinforce until unable so player won't have to spam reinforce and 
constantly watch animations. Is it possible to lower some animations?), 
stat clarification (What exactly do stats like +.18% attack speed even 
amount to and what does tough % even mean? I understand you have started up 
a wiki for stuff like this. You can go there if you press the little 
survival manual icon next to the chat button. It's still really new

high performance mean? Low performance lower game res for higher fps or low
